Variables:-
used to store data changes during program execution.

syntax:-
datatype variableName=value;

Local Variable-Declared inside block or method.
Instance Variable-Declared outside block and inside the class.
Static Variable-Declared with static keyword.
Final Variable-Declared with final keyword.

class Example {
    int instanceVar = 10;      // instance variable
    static int classVar = 20;  // static variable

    void method() {
        int localVar = 30;     // local variable
        final int CONSTANT = 40; // final variable
    }
}

Datatypes:-
byte b=10;
int i=500;
long l=10000L;
short s=100;
float f=5.5f;
double d=19.99;
char c='A';
boolean flag=true;

